title: One Key Reason Why The S&P 500 Doesn’t Fully Reflect The Economic Crisis
text: The relative winners from this crisis are overweighted in the S&P 500 and that's why the index isn't down as much as many expect.

title: Large-Cap ETFs Point To “Sell In May” Sell-Off
text: Negative fund flows out of the top ETFs by assets under management (AUM) point to potential dangers to current stocks valuations.

title: An Impressive April, Followed By Sell In May For US Stocks?
text: After a sharp rebound in valuations in April, are stocks ready to continue the rally into May?

title: Stocks are up against big 'resistance' and likely need actual economic improvement to overcome it
text: Much further upside from here probably requires more substantive indications of successful resumption of economic activity.

title: Stocks May Have Hit A Ceiling
text: Stocks had a great April, but it will be challenging for them to continue to rally. Earnings estimates continue to drop and current valuation multiples were last seen in late 2001.

title: Why “Sell in May” Looks So Alluring in 2020
text: Every year, there is a recurring mantra of “Sell in May and go away!” This is the belief that investors should exit the stock market ahead of summer and not return until the fall.

title: S&P 500 Weekly Update: The Bull Market Rally Stalls At Resistance
text: The S&P closes out April with the best gain in 30 years and not many believe in this market.

title: The Fed Doesn't Believe In A V-Shaped Recovery And Neither Should You
text: The Fed is warning of several risks to the economic recovery process including damaged labor market dynamics and the potential for a long and deep recession.
